One of the smallest municipalities in northern KZN, Mthonjaneni has been hit by COVID-19 cases. MTHONJANENI - Mthonjaneni Local Municipality in Melmoth KwaZulu-Natal has closed its doors following a COVID-19 outbreak in its premises. At least 19 staff members tested positive, including councillors. READ: COVID-19 deaths in SA climbs to 1625 There are, however, fears the number of COVID-19 cases could be higher because some test results are not yet out. KwaZulu-Natal has the fourth-highest number of cases after Western Cape, Gauteng, and the Eastern Cape. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.